J.R. Sahlberg, 1880: 24. Type locality: &quot;Tolstoinos, in littore arenoso fluminis Jenissej [= Tolstyy Nos, Taymyr Autonomous Okrug, Russia]&quot; (original citation). Holotype [by monotypy] (♂) in NRSS.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="520" pageNumber="521">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Sahlberg" baseAuthorityYear="1880" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Pterostichus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="520" pageNumber="521" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sublaevis">Pterostichus sublaevis</taxonomicName>
var. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="520" pageNumber="521">unicoloripes</emphasis>
Poppius, 1910: 335. Type locality: &quot;Chara-Ulach-Gebirgen [= Kharaulakhskiy Khrebet] an der 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Lena-Mündung">Lena-Muendung</normalizedToken>
, unweit der Insel Tit-ary [northern Siberia]&quot; (original citation). Syntype(s) location unknown (apparently not at ZMH according to 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Silfverberg’s">Silfverberg's</normalizedToken>
